<statement>
<p>What are the solutions to <m>\displaystyle-{\left({x}+{2}\right)}^{{2}}+{2}={0}</m>? <fillin characters="12" /></p>
<p>Round solutions to two decimal places.</p>

</statement>
<solution>
<p><ul><li>-0.59,-3.41</li></ul></p><p><m>\displaystyle-{\left({x}+{2}\right)}^{{2}}+{2}={0}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{\left({x}+{2}\right)}^{{2}}=-{2}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{\left({x}+{2}\right)}^{{2}}={2}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}+{2}=\pm{1.4142135623731}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}=-{2}\pm{1.4142135623731}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}=-{0.5857864376269},-{3.4142135623731}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}=-{0.59},-{3.41}</m></p>
</solution>
</myopenmath>

